        <h2 class="section-title" id="languages">Underrated Programming Languages</h2>

        <div class="languages-grid">
            <div class="lang-card">
                <div class="lang-header elixir">
                    <div class="lang-icon">Ex</div>
                    <h3 class="lang-name">Elixir</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-body">
                    <p class="lang-description">
                        A functional, concurrent language built on the Erlang VM, designed for building scalable and maintainable applications with elegant syntax.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="lang-stats">
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🏆</span>
                            <span>First appeared: 2011</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>👨‍💻</span>
                            <span>Creator: José Valim</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🔄</span>
                            <span>Paradigm: Functional</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="language-popularity">
                        <div class="popularity-label">Popularity:</div>
                        <div class="popularity-bar-container">
                            <div class="popularity-bar" style="width: 25%;"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="pros-cons">
                        <div class="pros">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👍</span>
                                <span>Advantages</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="pros-list">
                                <li>Fault-tolerant architecture</li>
                                <li>Immutability by default</li>
                                <li>Excellent concurrency model</li>
                                <li>Phoenix web framework</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cons">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👎</span>
                                <span>Challenges</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="cons-list">
                                <li>Smaller ecosystem</li>
                                <li>Learning curve for OTP</li>
                                <li>Limited mobile support</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="code-sample">
                        <div class="code-sample-header">
                            <span>📝</span>
                            <span>Hello World Example:</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <span class="code-keyword">defmodule</span> <span class="code-function">Greeting</span> <span class="code-keyword">do</span><br>
                            &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="code-keyword">def</span> <span class="code-function">hello</span> <span class="code-keyword">do</span><br>
                            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="code-string">"Hello, world!"</span><br>
                            &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="code-keyword">end</span><br>
                            <span class="code-keyword">end</span><br><br>
                            <span class="code-function">IO</span>.<span class="code-function">puts</span> <span class="code-function">Greeting</span>.<span class="code-function">hello</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tags">
                        <div class="tag">Web Development</div>
                        <div class="tag">Distributed Systems</div>
                        <div class="tag">Fault Tolerance</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-footer">
                    <div class="lang-rating">
                        <div class="rating-stars">★★★★☆</div>
                        <div class="rating-value">4.5/5</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="lang-links">
                        <a href="https://elixir-lang.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">🔗</a>
                        <a href="https://github.com/elixir-lang/elixir" class="lang-link" target="_blank">📦</a>
                        <a href="https://elixirforum.com/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">👥</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="lang-card">
                <div class="lang-header crystal">
                    <div class="lang-icon">Cr</div>
                    <h3 class="lang-name">Crystal</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-body">
                    <p class="lang-description">
                        A statically-typed language with Ruby-like syntax, offering the expressiveness of a dynamic language with the performance and safety of a compiled language.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="lang-stats">
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🏆</span>
                            <span>First appeared: 2014</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>👨‍💻</span>
                            <span>Creator: Manas Technology</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🔄</span>
                            <span>Paradigm: Object-oriented</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="language-popularity">
                        <div class="popularity-label">Popularity:</div>
                        <div class="popularity-bar-container">
                            <div class="popularity-bar" style="width: 20%;"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="pros-cons">
                        <div class="pros">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👍</span>
                                <span>Advantages</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="pros-list">
                                <li>Ruby-like elegant syntax</li>
                                <li>Compiled to native code</li>
                                <li>Static type checking</li>
                                <li>Built-in concurrency</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cons">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👎</span>
                                <span>Challenges</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="cons-list">
                                <li>Young ecosystem</li>
                                <li>Still evolving language</li>
                                <li>Limited IDE support</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="code-sample">
                        <div class="code-sample-header">
                            <span>📝</span>
                            <span>Hello World Example:</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <span class="code-comment"># Simple HTTP server</span><br>
                            <span class="code-keyword">require</span> <span class="code-string">"http/server"</span><br><br>
                            <span class="code-function">server</span> = <span class="code-type">HTTP</span>::<span class="code-type">Server</span>.<span class="code-function">new</span> <span class="code-keyword">do</span> |<span class="code-function">context</span>|<br>
                            &nbsp;&nbsp;context.<span class="code-function">response</span>.<span class="code-function">content_type</span> = <span class="code-string">"text/plain"</span><br>
                            &nbsp;&nbsp;context.<span class="code-function">response</span>.<span class="code-function">print</span> <span class="code-string">"Hello, world!"</span><br>
                            <span class="code-keyword">end</span><br><br>
                            <span class="code-function">puts</span> <span class="code-string">"Listening on http://127.0.0.1:8080"</span><br>
                            <span class="code-function">server</span>.<span class="code-function">listen</span>(<span class="code-string">"127.0.0.1"</span>, <span class="code-number">8080</span>)
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tags">
                        <div class="tag">High Performance</div>
                        <div class="tag">Web Development</div>
                        <div class="tag">Ruby-like</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-footer">
                    <div class="lang-rating">
                        <div class="rating-stars">★★★★☆</div>
                        <div class="rating-value">4.2/5</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="lang-links">
                        <a href="https://crystal-lang.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">🔗</a>
                        <a href="https://github.com/crystal-lang/crystal" class="lang-link" target="_blank">📦</a>
                        <a href="https://forum.crystal-lang.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">👥</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="lang-card">
                <div class="lang-header nim">
                    <div class="lang-icon">Nm</div>
                    <h3 class="lang-name">Nim</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-body">
                    <p class="lang-description">
                        A statically typed language with Python-like syntax that compiles to C, C++, or JavaScript, offering a unique blend of performance and readability.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="lang-stats">
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🏆</span>
                            <span>First appeared: 2008</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>👨‍💻</span>
                            <span>Creator: Andreas Rumpf</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🔄</span>
                            <span>Paradigm: Multi-paradigm</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="language-popularity">
                        <div class="popularity-label">Popularity:</div>
                        <div class="popularity-bar-container">
                            <div class="popularity-bar" style="width: 18%;"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="pros-cons">
                        <div class="pros">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👍</span>
                                <span>Advantages</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="pros-list">
                                <li>Python-like syntax</li>
                                <li>Compile-time metaprogramming</li>
                                <li>Excellent performance</li>
                                <li>Memory safety features</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cons">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👎</span>
                                <span>Challenges</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="cons-list">
                                <li>Small community</li>
                                <li>Limited package ecosystem</li>
                                <li>Less corporate backing</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="code-sample">
                        <div class="code-sample-header">
                            <span>📝</span>
                            <span>Hello World Example:</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <span class="code-comment"># Hello world in Nim</span><br>
                            <span class="code-keyword">proc</span> <span class="code-function">hello</span>(): <span class="code-type">string</span> =<br>
                            &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="code-keyword">return</span> <span class="code-string">"Hello, world!"</span><br>
                            <br>
                            <span class="code-keyword">echo</span> <span class="code-function">hello</span>()<br>
                            <br>
                            <span class="code-comment"># Concise version</span><br>
                            <span class="code-keyword">echo</span> <span class="code-string">"Hello, world!"</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tags">
                        <div class="tag">Systems Programming</div>
                        <div class="tag">Game Development</div>
                        <div class="tag">Metaprogramming</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-footer">
                    <div class="lang-rating">
                        <div class="rating-stars">★★★★☆</div>
                        <div class="rating-value">4.1/5</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="lang-links">
                        <a href="https://nim-lang.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">🔗</a>
                        <a href="https://github.com/nim-lang/Nim" class="lang-link" target="_blank">📦</a>
                        <a href="https://forum.nim-lang.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">👥</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="lang-card">
                <div class="lang-header ocaml">
                    <div class="lang-icon">Oc</div>
                    <h3 class="lang-name">OCaml</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-body">
                    <p class="lang-description">
                        A powerful functional language with a strong type system and efficient compiler, used for building reliable and efficient software in various domains.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="lang-stats">
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🏆</span>
                            <span>First appeared: 1996</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>👨‍💻</span>
                            <span>Creator: INRIA</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🔄</span>
                            <span>Paradigm: Multi-paradigm, Functional</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="language-popularity">
                        <div class="popularity-label">Popularity:</div>
                        <div class="popularity-bar-container">
                            <div class="popularity-bar" style="width: 22%;"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="pros-cons">
                        <div class="pros">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👍</span>
                                <span>Advantages</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="pros-list">
                                <li>Strong static type system</li>
                                <li>Excellent pattern matching</li>
                                <li>Used in finance and academia</li>
                                <li>Powerful module system</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cons">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👎</span>
                                <span>Challenges</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="cons-list">
                                <li>Steep learning curve</li>
                                <li>Limited library ecosystem</li>
                                <li>Not as popular in industry</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="code-sample">
                        <div class="code-sample-header">
                            <span>📝</span>
                            <span>Hello World Example:</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <span class="code-comment">(* Define a simple function *)</span><br>
                            <span class="code-keyword">let</span> <span class="code-function">hello</span> () = <span class="code-string">"Hello, world!"</span><br><br>
                            <span class="code-comment">(* Output the result *)</span><br>
                            <span class="code-keyword">let</span> () = <span class="code-function">print_endline</span> (<span class="code-function">hello</span> ())<br><br>
                            <span class="code-comment">(* Or more concisely *)</span><br>
                            <span class="code-keyword">let</span> () = <span class="code-function">print_endline</span> <span class="code-string">"Hello, world!"</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tags">
                        <div class="tag">Functional Programming</div>
                        <div class="tag">Type Safety</div>
                        <div class="tag">Finance</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-footer">
                    <div class="lang-rating">
                        <div class="rating-stars">★★★★☆</div>
                        <div class="rating-value">4.3/5</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="lang-links">
                        <a href="https://ocaml.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">🔗</a>
                        <a href="https://github.com/ocaml/ocaml" class="lang-link" target="_blank">📦</a>
                        <a href="https://discuss.ocaml.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">👥</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="lang-card">
                <div class="lang-header haskell">
                    <div class="lang-icon">Hs</div>
                    <h3 class="lang-name">Haskell</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-body">
                    <p class="lang-description">
                        A purely functional programming language with strong static typing, type inference, and lazy evaluation, known for its elegance and mathematical foundation.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="lang-stats">
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🏆</span>
                            <span>First appeared: 1990</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>👨‍💻</span>
                            <span>Creator: Committee</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🔄</span>
                            <span>Paradigm: Purely Functional</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="language-popularity">
                        <div class="popularity-label">Popularity:</div>
                        <div class="popularity-bar-container">
                            <div class="popularity-bar" style="width: 28%;"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="pros-cons">
                        <div class="pros">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👍</span>
                                <span>Advantages</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="pros-list">
                                <li>Strong mathematical foundation</li>
                                <li>Advanced type system</li>
                                <li>Pure functional programming</li>
                                <li>Lazy evaluation</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cons">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👎</span>
                                <span>Challenges</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="cons-list">
                                <li>Difficult learning curve</li>
                                <li>Performance unpredictability</li>
                                <li>Smaller job market</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="code-sample">
                        <div class="code-sample-header">
                            <span>📝</span>
                            <span>Hello World Example:</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <span class="code-comment">-- Simple hello world</span><br>
                            <span class="code-function">main</span> :: <span class="code-type">IO</span> ()<br>
                            <span class="code-function">main</span> = <span class="code-function">putStrLn</span> <span class="code-string">"Hello, world!"</span><br><br>
                            <span class="code-comment">-- A more functional approach</span><br>
                            <span class="code-function">hello</span> :: <span class="code-type">String</span><br>
                            <span class="code-function">hello</span> = <span class="code-string">"Hello, world!"</span><br><br>
                            <span class="code-function">main'</span> :: <span class="code-type">IO</span> ()<br>
                            <span class="code-function">main'</span> = <span class="code-function">putStrLn</span> <span class="code-function">hello</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tags">
                        <div class="tag">Functional Programming</div>
                        <div class="tag">Type Theory</div>
                        <div class="tag">Academia</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-footer">
                    <div class="lang-rating">
                        <div class="rating-stars">★★★★★</div>
                        <div class="rating-value">4.6/5</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="lang-links">
                        <a href="https://www.haskell.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">🔗</a>
                        <a href="https://github.com/haskell" class="lang-link" target="_blank">📦</a>
                        <a href="https://discourse.haskell.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">👥</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="lang-card">
                <div class="lang-header f-sharp">
                    <div class="lang-icon">F#</div>
                    <h3 class="lang-name">F#</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-body">
                    <p class="lang-description">
                        A functional-first language for the .NET ecosystem, combining functional programming with object-oriented features and practical tooling.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="lang-stats">
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🏆</span>
                            <span>First appeared: 2005</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>👨‍💻</span>
                            <span>Creator: Microsoft Research</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🔄</span>
                            <span>Paradigm: Functional, Object-oriented</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="language-popularity">
                        <div class="popularity-label">Popularity:</div>
                        <div class="popularity-bar-container">
                            <div class="popularity-bar" style="width: 30%;"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="pros-cons">
                        <div class="pros">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👍</span>
                                <span>Advantages</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="pros-list">
                                <li>Full .NET ecosystem access</li>
                                <li>Strong type inference</li>
                                <li>Excellent data processing</li>
                                <li>Concise syntax</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cons">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👎</span>
                                <span>Challenges</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="cons-list">
                                <li>In C#'s shadow</li>
                                <li>Smaller community</li>
                                <li>Less learning resources</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="code-sample">
                        <div class="code-sample-header">
                            <span>📝</span>
                            <span>Hello World Example:</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <span class="code-comment">// Simple hello world</span><br>
                            <span class="code-function">printfn</span> <span class="code-string">"Hello, world!"</span><br><br>
                            <span class="code-comment">// Using a function</span><br>
                            <span class="code-keyword">let</span> <span class="code-function">hello</span> () = <span class="code-string">"Hello, world!"</span><br><br>
                            <span class="code-comment">// Print the result</span><br>
                            <span class="code-function">hello</span> () |> <span class="code-function">printfn</span> <span class="code-string">"%s"</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tags">
                        <div class="tag">.NET Platform</div>
                        <div class="tag">Data Science</div>
                        <div class="tag">Functional Programming</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-footer">
                    <div class="lang-rating">
                        <div class="rating-stars">★★★★☆</div>
                        <div class="rating-value">4.4/5</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="lang-links">
                        <a href="https://fsharp.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">🔗</a>
                        <a href="https://github.com/dotnet/fsharp" class="lang-link" target="_blank">📦</a>
                        <a href="https://forums.fsharp.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">👥</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="lang-card">
                <div class="lang-header erlang">
                    <div class="lang-icon">Er</div>
                    <h3 class="lang-name">Erlang</h3>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-body">
                    <p class="lang-description">
                        A functional language designed for building massively scalable, distributed, fault-tolerant systems that can run for years without interruption.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="lang-stats">
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🏆</span>
                            <span>First appeared: 1986</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>👨‍💻</span>
                            <span>Creator: Ericsson</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lang-stat">
                            <span>🔄</span>
                            <span>Paradigm: Functional, Concurrent</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="language-popularity">
                        <div class="popularity-label">Popularity:</div>
                        <div class="popularity-bar-container">
                            <div class="popularity-bar" style="width: 24%;"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="pros-cons">
                        <div class="pros">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👍</span>
                                <span>Advantages</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="pros-list">
                                <li>Superior fault tolerance</li>
                                <li>Hot code swapping</li>
                                <li>Battle-tested in telecom</li>
                                <li>Actor model concurrency</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="cons">
                            <h4>
                                <span>👎</span>
                                <span>Challenges</span>
                            </h4>
                            <ul class="cons-list">
                                <li>Unusual syntax</li>
                                <li>Steep learning curve</li>
                                <li>Not for general apps</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="code-sample">
                        <div class="code-sample-header">
                            <span>📝</span>
                            <span>Hello World Example:</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="code-block">
                            <span class="code-comment">% Define a module</span><br>
                            -<span class="code-keyword">module</span>(<span class="code-function">hello</span>).<br>
                            -<span class="code-keyword">export</span>([<span class="code-function">start/0</span>]).<br><br>
                            <span class="code-comment">% Define the start function</span><br>
                            <span class="code-function">start</span>() -><br>
                            &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="code-function">io</span>:<span class="code-function">format</span>(<span class="code-string">"Hello, world!~n"</span>).<br><br>
                            <span class="code-comment">% To run: hello:start().</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="tags">
                        <div class="tag">Distributed Systems</div>
                        <div class="tag">Telecommunications</div>
                        <div class="tag">Fault Tolerance</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="lang-footer">
                    <div class="lang-rating">
                        <div class="rating-stars">★★★★☆</div>
                        <div class="rating-value">4.2/5</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="lang-links">
                        <a href="https://www.erlang.org/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">🔗</a>
                        <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp" class="lang-link" target="_blank">📦</a>
                        <a href="https://erlangforums.com/" class="lang-link" target="_blank">👥</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="quote-box">
            <p class="quote-text">
                "Sometimes the most elegant solutions come from the least expected places. Exploring underrated programming languages often reveals approaches to problems that mainstream languages haven't discovered yet."
            </p>
            <div class="quote-author">Dr. Maya Richards</div>
            <div class="quote-author-title">Professor of Computer Science, MIT</div>
        </div>

